illegitimate /ˌɪlɪˈdʒɪtɪmɪt/

1. ADJ A person who is illegitimate was born of parents who were not married to each other. 私生的 

例： They discovered he had an illegitimate child. 他们发现他有一个私生子。 

2. ADJ Illegitimate is used to describe activities and institutions that are not in accordance with the law or with accepted standards of what is right. 不合规则的; 不合法的 

例： He realized that, otherwise, the election would have been dismissed as illegitimate by the international community. 他意识到，不这样的话，选举就会被国际社会以不合法为由而不予承认。

